==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Persecution
<hw>Per`se*cu"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>pers⟦eacute⟧cution</ets>, L. <ets>persecutio</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or practice of persecuting; especially, the infliction of loss, pain, or death for adherence to a particular creed or mode of worship.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Persecution</qex> produces no sincere conviction.</q> <rj><qau>Paley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The state or condition of being persecuted.</def>  <rj><au>Locke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A carrying on; prosecution.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Persecutor</ent>⟦br⟧
